<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08023</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT TO ENHANCE THE TAXING POWERS OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT UNITS BY AMENDING CERTAIN PROVISIONS IN BOOK II OF REPUBLIC ACT 7160, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE LOCAL GOVERNMENT CODE OF 1991</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to increase the annual fixed tax rate for delivery trucks or vans of manufacturers or producers from P500 to P1,500;  reduce the taxable base of the head office from 30 % to 10 % of gross sales or revenues; increase the share of sales outlets and the likes from 70% to 90%; remove the authority of the national government to provides exemptions on local taxes, fees and charges;  and limit LGUs to provide local exemptions from taxes, fees and charges.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-06</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LOCAL GOVERNMENT ON 2018-08-08</td></tr></table>